Hello all,

I recently tried to do an experiment with plastic
synapses.  However, I had very little success.

The experiment was to simulate a bee finding a flower.
 The bee would begin its life at the hive and start
exploring until it found the flower.  If it succeeded
in finding the flower, the bee would be replaced at
the hive and the hope was that it would then find the
flower faster.

I set the fitness function to be two-fold.  First the
bee&#39;s fitness improved if it found the flower at all. 
Second, the bee&#39;s fitness improved if it found the
flower faster than the previous time.

I tried to force the bees to use the knowledge gained
during their lifetime by randomly moving the flower
after every generation.

The bees ended up developing a good search algorithm,
but never learned to use what they learned during
their lifetime.

It was very frustrating, and I gave up cause I really
want to graduate =)

By the way, is there anyone here who could help me out
on some backpropagation algorithms? 

Thanks!

-Chris

